## Architect Role (Chat Pane)

When Raf asks a backend question or wants to implement something, YOU own the plan:
1. Identify which controller/service/model is affected
2. Check conventions below before writing any code
3. Assign the Agent to implement тАФ never let it guess at patterns; point it to the right file
4. Review output for convention violations (money as float, inline OT, missing auth, etc.)
5. Run `php artisan test` (or scoped backend tests when appropriate) and report actual run results before closing any backend task

**Never let the Agent skip the auth check, use floats for money, or touch `am_earnings` values.**

